c: 9
v: 120
t: "It was not 斯proper撕 for the people of Medina and the nomadic Arabs around them to avoid marching with the Messenger of God or to prefer their own lives above his. That is because whenever they suffer from thirst, fatigue, or hunger in the cause of God; or tread on a territory, unnerving the disbelievers; or inflict any loss on an enemy鈥攊t is written to their credit as a good deed. Surely God never discounts the reward of the good-doers"